'''Rose''' is a common maid-name in [[the Shire]] and may refer to:

==Middle-earth==
* '''[[Roses]]''', fair-scented flowers found throughout [[Middle-earth]].
** [[Eglantine]], a type of rose found in [[Ithilien]].
** [[Rock-roses]], not a type of rose.
* [[Rosa Baggins]] (born {{SR|1256}}), great-grandmother of [[Peregrin Took]].
* [[Rose (daughter of Holman)|Rose]] (born {{SR|1262}}), daughter, and youngest child, of [[Holman the greenhanded]].
* '''[[Rose Cotton]] ({{SR|1384}} - {{SR|1482}}), daughter of [[Tolman Cotton Senior|Tom Cottom]] and the wife of [[Samwise Gamgee]].'''
** [[Rose Gardner]] (born {{SR|1425}}), third child of Rose Cotton and Samwise Gamgee.
** [[Primrose Gardner]] (born {{SR|1435}}), ninth child of Rose Cotton and Samwise Gamgee.
==Real World==
* [[Rose Anne Daniello]], author.
* [[Rose A. Zimbardo]], editor of ''[[Understanding The Lord of the Rings]]''.
